cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech processing and linguistic parsing. It may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech signals. Additionally, it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses deep neural networks for phonological posterior estimation. It may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as linguistic parsing is a problem in natural language processing and information retrieval. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses deep neural networks for speech processing.
